blonde or brunette looks vs maintenance and an identity crisis i've been blond most of my life but something has changed since i had my son it is getting harder and harder to get my hair a nice light golden blond my hair must be getting darker should i just bag the blondness and go with a dark golden brown that's kind of what my roots look like i like to consider myself low maintenance and down to earth brunette but also lots of fun blonde help well as a gal who has been the high maintenance of a fake blonde i know the hell it can be to have roots i can't imagine what that craziness would be like with the added stress of a new baby i personally would go for the natural shade your hair is growing in now if you are still craving those golden locks for yester years go to the stylist and get some very natural looking blonde highlights and remember we can have fun no matter what our haircolor is its all about personality and attitude work it girl Hair color Blond Supergirl Link (Legend of Zelda) The Ashlee Simpson Show W.I.T.C.H. Hair Melanin Gwen Stefani Dragon Booster Aristasia Red hair Human skin color The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Marilyn Monroe The Rasmus Saved by the Bell Race of Jesus Madonna (entertainer) Kender White (people) Joke Music of the United Kingdom (1950s and 60s) Sexuality and gender identity-based cultures Pamela Anderson Nadia: The Secret of Blue Water Bonus Stage Blood (computer game) Theory of conduct Blood on the Tracks Laser hair removal Pitaten Bock Gender role Jane Russell Wolfrider Characters in the Smurfs Black (people) The Marshall Mathers LP Hydrogen peroxide EastEnders Grunge music Pubic hair Characters of The Sandman Trigun Mobile Suit Gundam Wing Doug Afrocentrism Dawson's Creek Kodocha Irish dance Scrapped Princess Patricia Ford Humphrey Bogart Charlie Brown Josie and the Pussycats (comic) Futurama (TV series - season 5) Julie Brown D.N. Angel Ron and Fez Polar Bear Elemental spirits (Seiken Densetsu) Rock (music) Static Shock